22/** Provides different easing functions that can be used in blueprints */
23UENUM(BlueprintType)
24namespace EEasingFunc
25{
26 enum Type : int
27 {
28 /** Simple linear interpolation. */
29 Linear,
30
31 /** Simple step interpolation. */
32 Step,
33
34 /** Sinusoidal in interpolation. */
35 SinusoidalIn,
36
37 /** Sinusoidal out interpolation. */
38 SinusoidalOut,
39
40 /** Sinusoidal in/out interpolation. */
41 SinusoidalInOut,
42
43 /** Smoothly accelerates, but does not decelerate into the target. Ease amount controlled by BlendExp. */
44 EaseIn,
45
46 /** Immediately accelerates, but smoothly decelerates into the target. Ease amount controlled by BlendExp. */
47 EaseOut,
48
49 /** Smoothly accelerates and decelerates. Ease amount controlled by BlendExp. */
50 EaseInOut,
51
52 /** Easing in using an exponential */
53 ExpoIn,
54
55 /** Easing out using an exponential */
56 ExpoOut,
57
58 /** Easing in/out using an exponential method */
59 ExpoInOut,
60
61 /** Easing is based on a half circle. */
62 CircularIn,
63
64 /** Easing is based on an inverted half circle. */
65 CircularOut,
66
67 /** Easing is based on two half circles. */
68 CircularInOut,
69
70 };
71}

73/** Different methods for interpolating rotation between transforms */
74UENUM(BlueprintType)
75namespace ELerpInterpolationMode
76{
77 enum Type : int
78 {
79 /** Shortest Path or Quaternion interpolation for the rotation. */
80 QuatInterp,
81
82 /** Rotor or Euler Angle interpolation. */
83 EulerInterp,
84
85 /** Dual quaternion interpolation, follows helix or screw-motion path between keyframes. */
86 DualQuatInterp
87 };
88}

110USTRUCT(BlueprintType)
111struct FFloatSpringState
112{
113 GENERATED_BODY()
114
115 float PrevTarget;
116 float Velocity;
117 bool bPrevTargetValid;
118
119 FFloatSpringState()
120 : PrevTarget(0.f)
121 , Velocity(0.f)
122 , bPrevTargetValid(false)
123 {
124 }
125
126 void Reset()
127 {
128 PrevTarget = Velocity = 0.f;
129 bPrevTargetValid = false;
130 }
131};
132
133USTRUCT(BlueprintType)
134struct FVectorSpringState
135{
136 GENERATED_BODY()
137
138 FVector PrevTarget;
139 FVector Velocity;
140 bool bPrevTargetValid;
141
142 FVectorSpringState()
143 : PrevTarget(FVector::ZeroVector)
144 , Velocity(FVector::ZeroVector)
145 , bPrevTargetValid(false)
146 {
147 }
148
149 void Reset()
150 {
151 PrevTarget = Velocity = FVector::ZeroVector;
152 bPrevTargetValid = false;
153 }
154};
155
156USTRUCT(BlueprintType)
157struct FQuaternionSpringState
158{
159 GENERATED_BODY()
160
161 FQuat PrevTarget;
162 FVector AngularVelocity;
163 bool bPrevTargetValid;
164
165 FQuaternionSpringState()
166 : PrevTarget(FQuat::Identity)
167 , AngularVelocity(FVector::ZeroVector)
168 , bPrevTargetValid(false)
169 {
170 }
171
172 void Reset()
173 {
174 PrevTarget = FQuat::Identity;
175 AngularVelocity = FVector::ZeroVector;
176 bPrevTargetValid = false;
177 }
178};

528
529 /** Custom thunk to allow script stack trace in case of modulo by zero */
530 DECLARE_FUNCTION(execPercent_FloatFloat)
531 {
532 P_GET_PROPERTY(FDoubleProperty, A);
533 P_GET_PROPERTY(FDoubleProperty, B);
534
535 P_FINISH;
536
537 if (B == 0.f)
538 {
539 FFrame::KismetExecutionMessage(*FString::Printf(TEXT("Modulo by zero detected: %f %% 0\n%s"), A, *Stack.GetStackTrace()), ELogVerbosity::Warning);
540 *(double*)RESULT_PARAM = 0;
541 return;
542 }
543
544 *(double*)RESULT_PARAM = GenericPercent_FloatFloat(A, B);
545 }

1342 /**
1343 * Return the Quaternion orientation corresponding to the direction in which the vector points.
1344 * Similar to the FRotator version, returns a result without roll such that it preserves the up vector.

1346 * @note If you don't care about preserving the up vector and just want the most direct rotation, you can use the faster

1773 * Uses a simple spring model to interpolate a vector from Current to Target.
1774 *
1775 * @param Current Current value
1776 * @param Target Target value
1777 * @param SpringState Data related to spring model (velocity, error, etc..) - Create a unique variable per spring
1778 * @param Stiffness How stiff the spring model is (more stiffness means more oscillation around the target value)
1779 * @param CriticalDampingFactor How much damping to apply to the spring (0 means no damping, 1 means critically damped which means no oscillation)
1780 * @param DeltaTime Time difference since the last update
1781 * @param Mass Multiplier that acts like mass on a spring
1782 * @param TargetVelocityAmount If 1 then the target velocity will be calculated and used, which results following the target more closely/without lag. Values down to zero (recommended when using this to smooth data) will progressively disable this effect.
1783 * @param bClamp Whether to use the Min/Max values to clamp the motion
1784 * @param MinValue Clamps the minimum output value and cancels the velocity if it reaches this limit
1785 * @param MaxValue Clamps the maximum output value and cancels the velocity if it reaches this limit
1786 * @param bInitializeFromTarget If set then the current value will be set from the target on the first update
1787 */
1788 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta = (ScriptMethod = "InterpSpringTo", Keywords = "position", AdvancedDisplay = "8"), Category = "Math|Interpolation")
1789 static ENGINE_API FVector VectorSpringInterp(FVector Current, FVector Target, UPARAM(ref) FVectorSpringState& SpringState,
1790 float Stiffness, float CriticalDampingFactor, float DeltaTime,
1791 float Mass = 1.f, float TargetVelocityAmount = 1.f,
1792 bool bClamp = false, FVector MinValue = FVector(-1.f), FVector MaxValue = FVector(1.f),
1793 bool bInitializeFromTarget = false);

4110 /**
4111 * Uses a simple spring model to interpolate a float from Current to Target.
4112 *
4113 * @param Current Current value
4114 * @param Target Target value
4115 * @param SpringState Data related to spring model (velocity, error, etc..) - Create a unique variable per spring
4116 * @param Stiffness How stiff the spring model is (more stiffness means more oscillation around the target value)
4117 * @param CriticalDampingFactor How much damping to apply to the spring (0 means no damping, 1 means critically damped which means no oscillation)
4118 * @param DeltaTime Time difference since the last update
4119 * @param Mass Multiplier that acts like mass on a spring
4120 * @param TargetVelocityAmount If 1 then the target velocity will be calculated and used, which results following the target more closely/without lag. Values down to zero (recommended when using this to smooth data) will progressively disable this effect.
4121 * @param bClamp Whether to use the Min/Max values to clamp the motion
4122 * @param MinValue Clamps the minimum output value and cancels the velocity if it reaches this limit
4123 * @param MaxValue Clamps the maximum output value and cancels the velocity if it reaches this limit
4124 * @param bInitializeFromTarget If set then the current value will be set from the target on the first update
4125 */
4126 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "Math|Interpolation", meta=(AdvancedDisplay = "8"))
4127 static ENGINE_API float FloatSpringInterp(float Current, float Target, UPARAM(ref) FFloatSpringState& SpringState,
4128 float Stiffness, float CriticalDampingFactor, float DeltaTime,
4129 float Mass = 1.f, float TargetVelocityAmount = 1.f,
4130 bool bClamp = false, float MinValue = -1.f, float MaxValue = 1.f,
4131 bool bInitializeFromTarget = false);

4329 /**
4330 * Finds the minimum area rectangle that encloses a set of coplanar points.
4331 * Uses the exhaustive search algorithm in http://www.geometrictools.com/Documentation/MinimumAreaRectangle.pdf
4332 *
4333 * @param WorldContextObject - Pointer to world context; only used when debug draw is enabled
4334 * @param InPoints - Points to enclose in the rectangle; need to be within the same plane for correct results
4335 * @param SampleSurfaceNormal - Normal indicating the surface direction for the points
4336 * @param OutRectCenter - Translation for the output rectangle from the origin
4337 * @param OutRectRotation - Rotation for the output rectangle from the XY plane
4338 * @param OutRectLengthX - Length of the output rectangle along the X axis before rotation
4339 * @param OutRectLengthY - Length of the output rectangle along the Y axis before rotation
4340 * @param bDebugDraw - Draws the output rectangle for debugging purposes provided the world context is set as well
4341 */
4342 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Math|Geometry", meta=(WorldContext="WorldContextObject", CallableWithoutWorldContext))
